Aruna Jothivel

 attended 

 posted on 13 Aug, 2016

					""Tamil Classes-Madam has a very unique way of teaching a child,She goes by the child's mood.A little girl as 41/2 yrs. If the child is interested to play during the class hours, Madam would go ahead play with the child & teach.
When my daughter started to learn Tamil,Madam used to write one big  alphabet on a paper & the child would write over the same alphabet with different color pencils. This would not only save paper but also attract the child to write more.
Madam used methods like flash cards, singing song & dancing for the song with which the child's grasping power increased,she even taught Tamil months along with exercise so that the child would remember & be attentive during class hours.Madam also made her ready small one line story  book with lots of pictures on them, She would help the child go by the letters which the child can ready with her guidance.My daughter with all her help and support try  reading a word on the book word by word . Now she can ready is able to ready some words on the wall posters too!
Abacus Classes: Very interesting , My child new numbers only from 1-50. After joining the in Abacus she is trying to do better. 
Rubik Cubes:Me  & My husband was surprised to she my daughter   do the cubes with formula.Madam is very dedicated , interested to teach the child .She even gives so much of her time to make the child learn.My Daughter is very gifted to be mounded by her teaching's.
Now my daughter is learning over Skype,as we have moved to U.S.A

Vogue Institute Of Fashion Technology,,Richmond Road,Bangalore,India,560025,"Since the inception in the year 1996, Vogue institute of fashion technology has traveled an illustrious journey, thriving on its initial objective and promise of imparting Industry Specific education to today's youth. The institution has been focusing in providing training that promotes employable skills, and enhances social relevance. The institution imparts training of various academic programs right through vocational to post graduation level, specializing in Design, Management and technology. Vogue Institute of Fashion Technology's new campus is an architecture and design marvel, built with state-of-the art postmodern amenities. It is located in the elite Apparel Park, a revered and prime project of Karnataka Government, housing approximately around 75 textile and apparel giants. The institution provides industry exposure, along with technical and practical field knowledge with assured placements. The new campus in Apparel Park has a technologically advanced Smart campus, highly equipped with international standard design laboratories for Textile, Pattern Making, Jewellery Making and Sewing among many others. Varsha

 attended 

 posted on 08 Jun, 2016

					""I joined  this collage in January of last year and I loved it. It had it's minor dramas, but if you can ignore that crap (which you'll get at any institutes) and focus on your program you'll be fine. And it'll be over before you know it! I loved that they used a different instructor for each course, which I've heard isn't the case for most of these schools. I took the Interior designing course and loved it. 

They're very understanding if you're going through anything major like I unfortunately did, and they will work with you as long as you communicate with them. I just wish I hadn't let my unfortunate event take over my life completely as I'm positive I could have easily been hired somewhere after completing my hours required for extern. There are still days that I wonder if I could walk back in, explain myself, and start over...ANYWAYS, that's a totally different story.

Made some awesome friends throughout my time there too, I looked forward to going every day :)
									""', u'K

Mohan

 attended 

 in Jun,2014
					
 posted on 01 Jun, 2015

					""This is Mohan Raj, a student of CA final. For last 4 attempts I was appearing for CA final for both the groups after taking coaching classes from a big academy in Bangalore. Even after all my efforts I was not able to clear the exam, either failing in individual papers or in aggregate.

Someone told me that Rohit Sir takes personal tuition for CA final. I thought let me make the last attempt with personal tuition, if that can make the difference. Initially I had the doubt as what can be taught over Skype, but then I enrolled for his personal Skype class for the Nov? 14 session as I didn?t find any other way by which I can have personal focus from the teacher.

I took classes for all practical papers namely, Financial Reporting, SFM, Direct taxes, Costing and Indirect taxes. It took me 1-2 classes to adjust and thereafter it was very smooth and interesting. At the 1st class of every paper, he gauged my level and then accordingly tailored it to suit my needs.

His expertise is unmatched. The way he deals with the Accounting Standards and the way he connects the AS with Income tax and Company Law is exemplary. AS never looked so easy to me, earlier. If you have solid grip over AS then we all know that half the battle is won. His notes for the FR incl. AS are superb. 

His command over direct taxes and the way he teaches must be appreciated. Direct taxes which is another very tough paper for final was appealing to me after taking sir?s class. He starts from the toughest portion of paper which is Assessment and connected things. Again, His notes are highly exam oriented.

His notes for Strategic FM are awesome. He comprehensively deals with CAPM, Capital Budgeting and rationing. I never had any problem in dealing with practical paper like this, through Skype. I simply love the varied examples that he gives from real life. He made this paper very exciting.

To my surprise he even had the same depth of knowledge even for indirect taxes and Costing. Although I had not taken classes for audit and company law but he guided me on the way to approach these papers.

I sincerely thank Rohit Sir from the core of my heart as I cleared both the groups of CA final after taking his classes.

He is a wonderful person and someone who really inspires you to do your best. My experience was phenomenal and I highly recommend him for CA final. Thank You, UrbanPro.
									""', u'E

column5:
English",Anjanapura,Bangalore,India,560062,"My subject is Mathematics which is ""King of all subjects and queen of science"".  The most effective way to make mathematics enjoyable is to create a community in which students feel comfortable.  I begin with an ""anticipatory set"" by motivating my lectures through a series of examples, then I present definitions and theorems by providing equations and diagrams, as every student has a different learning style.  Some students grasp theory quickly while others require concrete examples and some feel comfortable by visual explanations and requires pictures.  I try to keep all of this in mind during lecturing.  In teaching I strive to convey my enthusiasm for the subject, clearly articulate the material and probe the connections between the new concepts and background knowledge.  My students want to arrive at the ""right answer"", while I want to emphasize though process required to arrive at the answer.  I encourage group work by the students with the worksheets after the completion of each chapter which is beneficial to both the strong students and those who are struggling.  At last importantly I make my students aware that I am there to support them in their effort in the course as they transition from ""DOING MATHS"" to ""LEARNING MATHS"".",[],"['Art and Craft
                           
                               classes', 'BA Tuition', 'BSc Tuition', 'BCom Tuition', 'Class IX-X Tuition', 'Class XI-XII Tuition (PUC)', 'Class VI-VIII Tuition', 'CET Coaching

 posted on 16 Apr, 2015

					""I attended Eggless baking course. 
The fees amount is very high (around 13500Rs after 10% discount) for the items they teach. I had to agree for this to adjust my dates, one-to-one session and they quoted more items compared to other IBCA institute(when specifically asked). I had also mentioned I was a beginner.

IBCA institute offers the same items in Egg-free baking but for just 5k. 
But they offer only on week days and as per their calendar schedules.

Feedback:

First day: Breads and bread rolls (Good)
I could knead the dough and learn some roll knots, butter/milk washing, basic flavouring(garlic, rosemary+raisin breads).
What was expected more? Some explanation about how yeast/baking powder/soda affect bread/cake rising. What actions/ingredients make bad breads? (IBCA mentions this in their course)

Second day: Apple pie, Lemon tart, fruit lolly pop and Tea cake
I made the pastry/batter for all these. The chefs also mention some tips/tricks. But there is a lot of tricks in the temperatures in different OTGs/Convection ovens. The chef knows his OTG and could make the tea cake well. When tried at home, the cake sank in the middle(in my oven).

Third day: Sponge cake, Chocochip cookies, Vanilla/Chocolate(black forest) cake, cup cakes, Basic decorations
These are the important things for me. But all these were a flop. This day I was allowed just to measure and fold. All the cakes sank in the middle, became hard and tasted burnt. So I could never understand how to avoid an egg-free cake from falling in the mid. The cookie was soggy even after cooling. About decoration, the cakes were adjusted with pieces for learning layering (1-2 layers reduced cake was not spongy and fell). However I could understand some basic decoration.

So, I had to still rely on google and my experimentation to understand what can be made to avoid falling.
They don't give the certificate soon after the course is over. They claimed they resent twice, but I never received. I couldn't believe they even sent it. This was the first time someone had to resend to my office address. Finally my wife collected it personally.

Overall feedback: 
1. The chefs were patient enough to answer my questions. 
2. This course is not even worth 5k. The items taught are less compared to IBCA. The admin claimed it is too high because of one-to-one teaching and ingredients would be more. For these reasons, one can pay 1-2k more but not more than double. I can recommend this course if the price is appropriate and all the items they claim to teach come out well at least in their presence (at least the important ones).""', u'M

					""I am learning Hindustani classical music in this music school from almost last 6 months.And this 6months of musical journey has been really inspirational for me. The most great thing about the school is the mentors are giving attention to each and every student.They are paying attention to individual's problem and helping us to bring out the best. Before coming to this school I only knew that there are 7 notes we use to sing but now I have started analyzing the notes what are their importance how they sound. Nishaath

 attended 

 posted on 31 Aug, 2016

					""I have been taking Hindustani Classical vocal lessons from Sangeet Sadhana for about seven months now and have both learned a lot and have had a great time while learning. 
School provides very home like comfort and provides emphasis on making fundamentals of singing solid. Equal importance is given to theoretical knowledge of Hindustani classical music. The academy actively promotes various forms of classical and semi-classical music like bandish, bhajan, tarana, thumri, khayal, just to name a few. This school follows the true tradition of Guru-Shishya parampara. It has a consistent standard of teaching, thereby inculcating technical finesse and discipline among its students. Also, it?s a good thing that the school does not adhere to a particular gharana (In Hindustani music, each gharana represents a distinct style). The best from each gharana is chosen and taught to us.
All the teachers at the school have a laid back approach and allow the student to progress at his or her own pace. Teaching styles are very unique and comfortable. Lessons are revised time and again till each and every student gets the hang of it. Assessments are conducted to diagnose strength and weakness of students and eventually to improve their performance.
I would highly recommend this school to anyone who is interested in learning Hindustani vocal music.
									""']"

My son is currently in 12th standard and aspiring to clear IIT examinations to be held in 2015. For the Mathematics subject, I am sure that he is under the right umbrella. The coaching of Mathematics Hothouse is of immense help to him.
I recommend Mathematics Hothouse to those who want to reach beyond excellence in Mathematics.
""']"

column5:
English",Whitefield,Bangalore,India,560066,"I have been taking tutions/coaching classes since my graduation days, and now it has become my passion. It give me immense pleasure when my students succeed in their endeavor. So far it has been a learning experience for me, by sharing my knowledge and gaining knowledge from the students as well. I believe in rigorous training when it comes to my students, not being a bookworm but a smart student.   I approach tutoring in such a way that I show the students the basics, and then give them a variety of practice exercises and urge them figure out the answers themselves. If in doubt, I would keep prompting them to find the right answers thereby helping them to grasp the right concepts. .I believe in giving clear idea of concepts and rigorous practice to my students. It is important for a student to learn how to think and not merely be spoon fed. I believe in inciting them to develop a thought driven process in their learning and also develop a practical approach towards education where they learn from real life examples and incidents and not just theory in the books.Personalized and result driven approach are essential ingredients for effective tutoring. column5: English",Bilekahalli,Bangalore,India,560076,"I am a professional Badminton Coach and been coaching children for the past 5 Years. I am coaching in a nearby school thus helping the School  as well as interested children for taking up the game of Badminton seriously as their career. Few of my students have achieved laurels in the school competitions and few have migrated to higher levels of the game in pursuit of taking this as a professional career. The training given by us to the students are in line with Badminton World Federation (BWF) and major focus during the initial stages will be on fitness, stamina that are required for the game. Children from the age of 5 and above can start their preliminary training. Children starting from age 5 and above will be introduced to the game gradually so that they gain natural affinity towards the game thus avoiding initial burn-out factor.  attended 

 posted on 10 Mar, 2016

					""If there is any beginner who wants to learn the basics of photography, Gopu Krishnan definitely is a worthy choice !

I really enjoyed the Course. it was more like an Interaction between two photography enthusiasts. I was completely new to photography and dint even know anything about it. Gopu helped me with getting familiar with the DSLR first, the buttons and what are their use.then we learned the basic concepts of photography starting with Exposure, followed by Aperture, Shutter speed and ISO. then we looked at the different modes in the camera and how and when to shoot with them. we also dealt with few things to be done and not to be done while photographing a subject.

This was an amazing experience for me and i now know to click better pics,and as he rightly said this course was just the start and lot more needs to be done by practicing and gaining knowledge through other sources as well. Thanks Buddy.

VISHESH

 attended 

 posted on 28 Sep, 2015

					""Our Robotics class is very good class .We make models ,circuits & many other things such as mators . On the first day ,When our teachers shopwed us the demo ,I wasvery much interested about it . Therefore I asked my parents to join me to the class. On the first day of the class, we made the GEAR TRAIN . It was a train which was made of many GEAR 's& it was running on a gear track.Next day we made a TANKER. Third day we made MARCHING ROBOT .And on the fourth day we made a catapult. This was the end of the Elementary Physics. ONn the next day we started to do many circuits including GRIP SCOPE LED Flasher,Hand steadynes cTester & many other circuits.THis was the end of the ELECTRONICS. From the next day we started the ROBOTICS . First we made EXPLORER, then RADAR& DOOR ALARM, and also 3-SPEED TRANSMISSION WITH CLUCTH.Finally on the last day we made CHECK OUT SCANNER, While doing the models & circuits we shared good time with our teachers & our friends.""']"

Educadd,,Banashankari 3rd Stage,Bangalore,India,560085,"EduCADD is an ISO 9001 : 2008 Certified CAD/CAM/CAE, Multimedia & Project Management Company headquarters in Bangalore. In existence for over 15 years we offer end to end solutions in CAD (Computer Aided Design), CAE (Computer Aided Engineering) and CAM (Computer Aided Manufacturing). To meet the growing demand in CAD/CAM/CAE industry and to meet our expansion plans we committed to Franchising model in 2004. Since then we have carefully and strategically spread our wings to over 40 locations in India and abroad. Exponential growth in the economy and new developments in CAD/CAM/CAE in the last decade has created a very competitive market place for job seekers and employers alike. We at EduCADD realized the wide skill gap between fresh engineers and the caliber of people required by industry. Most of our engineers are not ready for the industry even after scoring higher grades in UG program. Quality training delivery, better training techniques and tools and industry internships are the key to address the issue. Our Courses and its innovative training approach covers in-depth understanding to various industry verticals like Mechanical, Civil, Architectural, Electrical, Automotive, Aerospace, Shipbuilding, Heavy & General Engineering Industries and enables the students to have hands on experience. EduCADD has wide range of courses that are designed to meet the needs of businesses in different domains. Over a decade plus of experience enables us to provide excellent training solutions for students.  posted on 13 Jul, 2016

					""It is very good institute in Bangalore if people are serious about learning any musical instrument. I am keyboard student and I have improved a lot in terms of basic of music, rhythm, pitch. Excellent guidance by Anthony sir.
									""', u'S












Shreyas

 attended 

 posted on 07 Jul, 2016

					""I had taken up guitar classes in creative institute. To share a few things about my experience, I should say it was a very nice atmosphere to learn something. The teacher was very nice, calm and composed when he teaches us.  Enough time is given for your practice. Individual attention for each student is given. Overall it is something I would recommend one to join !
									""', u'A












Anirudh

 attended 

 posted on 06 Jul, 2016

					""I have been with Creative Institute of Music for over a year now and can confidently say that I have learnt a great deal from Vivek. The classes are structured in a manner to make it easy to learn and comprehend. They are generous in imparting knowledge and approach teaching in a very calm manner. The atmosphere is also conducive to learning. 
The classes and the instructors approach the respective arts coherently. In that they not only deal with learning music or instruments but they also engage with you to procure good instruments and accessories and advise you on that as well; which is really important more so for beginners. 
I enjoy my time at the institute and spend the weekdays looking forward to attending classes! 

I strongly recommend Creative Institute for anyone aspiring to learn music or instruments or other arts.
									""']"

 posted on 02 Nov, 2014

					""I learnt basic Kannada under Manjunath Guruji in Dec-13 to Jan-14. I had a great experience learning basic Kannada under his tutelage. 

Classes and lessons are divided very well. There are video clips, nice little book with self exercises. 

He and his wife both conduct classes. Both are very cordial , punctual genuinely interested in teaching. Each session is an hour long and starts with meditation which sets nice mood for the session. Both are always available and attentive. They make sure you have thoroughly understood previous part before moving ahead.

I had no understanding of Kannada before tuition. My Kannada understanding dramatically improved after classes. 

Though I have relocated to Pune, I will always go back to study book given by Manjunatha Guruji to refresh Kannada whenever I have to visit Bengaluru in future !

In today?s increasingly competitive and advanced environment, a lot of emphasis is on innovative ability and extra customer delivered value which could differentiate the best from others. TIM?s training courses have been designed keeping in mind the industry needs and international standards, for individuals, who to make a career in the Travel-Tourism, Hospitality and Cargo-courier industry and are constantly updated to meet the changing demands. All these courses are technology and customer driven, designed to suite the student?s time and budget, following the highest standards and above all recognized by the industry in India and abroad. TIM is committed to provide job-oriented training to young, enthusiastic and hard-working graduates and post graduates students. Apart from technical skills TIM also aims to provide training for personality development and communication skills for the over-all development of the student.",[],['Air hostess\n                           \n                               Classes'],https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/member/photo/810599-medium190ap.jpg,[]

Hrishikesh Kumar

 attended 

 posted on 02 May, 2016

					""5/5
I wanted to gain weight. I was at first hesitant to consult a personal trainer thinking that it would be impossible for me to gain weight since I have been trying for a long time. Good that I finally did. 

The diet prescribed by Vikas is absolutely what your body needs. I liked the fact that he first studied my stamina and how my body reacted on my first ever workout. I've gained quite a substantial amount of weight in about a month. 

The workout is completely dynamic. We first started with 3kgs dumbbells, and within a month, my workout has upgraded to lifting 10kgs dumbbells. I could never have lifted 10kgs dumbbells at the start of the training. Overall my stamina has increased, thanks to Vikas's prescribed diet and supervised intensive workouts. The workouts are also quite entertaining too. As for me, I always look forward to the workout days. 

While working out, you may feel like giving up; fear not. Vikas will keep motivating you. Start training today with Vikas. I totally recommend it.

column5: Kannada",Bannerghatta Main Road,Bangalore,India,560076,"I've been working out for more than 3 years. My journey started when I got really disgusted by my weight and appearance. Made a conscious decision to change it and so far the journey has been rewarding :D I've learnt so many things, made mistakes and i'm still learning. I love helping people out because I had no one to help me and I don't want that to happen to people who really need the help. Currently i'm training 3 of my friends and they totally depend upon me for their fitness needs. (Both blessing and a curse :P) If you feel you have lost all hope, don't worry I went from 80 kgs (my worst) to 63 kgs (my best) all through self learning and hard work and I can help you with all your needs (Fitness regime, diet etc) without you having to worry about what to do except for following everything that I say to the letter. TENT CINEMA,,Banashankari 2nd Stage,Bangalore,India,560070,"Acting becomes an organic process of describing the world, and of relating to it an extremely authentic and physical manner. A group of students asked to describe a cup of coffee, for example, initially tried shaping themselves in the form of a glass. Going back to it again, they realized the idea was conveyed more subtly and easily by simply miming holding a hot cup, taking a sip, and placing it on an imaginary table.The exercises in class encourage students to think of themselves as artists by being open and transparent to the world around them. This is achieved by first breaking the often-imperceptible walls people have created within themselves. In one such exercise, the teacher steps out of the class and the students are asked to make as much noise as they can. Their aim must be to scream, shout, yell, laugh, and stomp around so loud it could bring the roof down! People are always expected to be quiet and maintain a certain amount of decorum. This exercise helps them breaks those expectations and allows them to be free.","['https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46860-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46861-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46862-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46863-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46864-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46865-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46866-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46867-large.jpg', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/photo/46868-large.jpg', '/bangalore/tent-cinema-banashankari-2nd-stage/gallery/5009822']","['Acting

column1: Bornfree Art School,,Jayanagar 3rd Block,Bangalore,India,560011,"There are 217 million working children in the world, 134 million of which live and word in India. These children toil for adults' profits and are deprived of the fundamental human right to education. Working children have no homes and attend no schools; they instead roam the streets and sleep under the stars. They belong to the most oppressed section of the society. In India, child labour is prohibited under the United Nations Convention of the Rights of the Child as well as the domestic law entitled the Child Labour Prohibition Act, 1986. However, child labour is socially, politically, economically and culturally systemized and practiced all over India. We need to bring about a social and cultural change in the mindset of the people and create an ever-growing community committed to the cause of creating an egalitarian society free of toiling children. Until we take up the task of educating and empowering our children, changes in the social pattern will become a distant dream. It is through the expressive idiom of the plastic and visual arts; theater, dance, mime, song and music and dialogue",[],['Acting\n                           \n                               classes'],https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/member/photo/1608152-medium190ap.jpeg,[]
